msgctxt "#30022"
msgid "How to get a token"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#30023"
msgid "Paste your SoundCloud OAuth token here to access your likes, playlists, following and reposts. See \"How to get a token\" below."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#30024"
msgid "OAuth token is invalid or expired. Please update it in Settings."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#30025"
msgid "You need to configure an OAuth token to access your profile. Opening settings now..."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "#30026"
msgid "To get your OAuth token:

1. Open https://soundcloud.com in Chrome or Firefox and sign in (verify your avatar shows top-right).

2. Press F12 to open the developer tools.

3. Go to the \"Network\" tab.

4. In the filter box, type: api-v2

5. Reload the page (F5).

6. Click on any request in the list (e.g. \"me\" or \"featured-tracks\").

7. In the right panel, scroll to \"Request Headers\".

8. Find the line: Authorization: OAuth XXXXXXXXX

9. Copy ONLY what comes after \"OAuth \" (the token itself, no prefix, no space).

10. Paste it in the \"OAuth token\" field of the addon settings.

11. Click \"Test OAuth token\" to verify.

Common pitfalls:
- Do NOT copy the cookie named \"oauth_token\" (under Application > Cookies). It looks similar but is rejected by the API.
- Do NOT include the word \"OAuth\" or any space at the start.
- The token expires periodically — when it does, repeat the steps to get a fresh one."
msgstr "To get your OAuth token:

1. Open https://soundcloud.com in Chrome or Firefox and sign in (verify your avatar shows top-right).

2. Press F12 to open the developer tools.

3. Go to the \"Network\" tab.

4. In the filter box, type: api-v2

5. Reload the page (F5).

6. Click on any request in the list (e.g. \"me\" or \"featured-tracks\").

7. In the right panel, scroll to \"Request Headers\".

8. Find the line: Authorization: OAuth XXXXXXXXX

9. Copy ONLY what comes after \"OAuth \" (the token itself, no prefix, no space).

10. Paste it in the \"OAuth token\" field of the addon settings.

11. Click \"Test OAuth token\" to verify.

Common pitfalls:
- Do NOT copy the cookie named \"oauth_token\" (under Application > Cookies). It looks similar but is rejected by the API.
- Do NOT include the word \"OAuth\" or any space at the start.
- The token expires periodically — when it does, repeat the steps to get a fresh one."

